<inglise> DIRECTIVE 1999/34/EC OF THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND OF THE COUNCIL of 10 May 1999 amending Council Directive 85/374/EEC on the approximation of the laws, regulations and administrative provisions of the Member States concerning liability for defective products </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA PARLAMENDI JA N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 1999/34/E&Uuml;, millega muudetakse n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi 85/374/EM&Uuml; liikmesriikide tootevastutust k&auml;sitlevate &otilde;igusnormide &uuml;htlustamise kohta 10. mai 1999 </eesti>
<inglise> THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA PARLAMENT JA EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 95 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eelk&otilde;ige selle artiklit 95, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission(1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee(2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 251 of the Treaty(3), </inglise>
<eesti> tehes otsuse asutamislepingu artiklis 251 s&auml;testatud korras (3) </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas product safety and compensation for damage caused by defective products are social imperatives which must be met within the internal market; whereas the Community has responded to those requirements by means of Directive 85/374/EEC(4) and Council Directive 92/59/EEC of 29 June 1992 on general product safety(5); </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: 1) tooteohutus ja puudusega toodete p&otilde;hjustatud kahju h&uuml;vitamine on &uuml;hiskondlikud n&otilde;uded, mida siseturul tuleb t&auml;ita; &uuml;hendus on neile n&otilde;uetele vastanud direktiiviga 85/374/EM&Uuml; (4) ja n&otilde;ukogu 29. juuni 1992. aasta direktiiviga 92/59/EM&Uuml; &uuml;ldise tooteohutuse kohta; (5) </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas Directive 85/374/EEC established a fair apportionment of the risks inherent in a modern society in which there is a high degree of technicality; whereas that Directive therefore struck a reasonable balance between the interests involved, in particular the protection of consumer health, encouraging innovation and scientific and technological development, guaranteeing undistorted competition and facilitating trade under a harmonised system of civil liability; whereas that Directive has thus helped to raise awareness among traders of the issue of product safety and the importance accorded to it; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) direktiiv 85/374/EM&Uuml; kehtestas k&otilde;rge tehnilisusem&auml;&auml;raga n&uuml;&uuml;dis&uuml;hiskonnale omaste riskide &otilde;iglase jaotamise; seet&otilde;ttu l&otilde;i see direktiiv m&otilde;istliku tasakaalu h&otilde;lmatud huvide, eriti tarbijate tervise kaitse, uuenduste ning teadusliku ja tehnilise arengu edendamise, moonutamata konkurentsi tagamise ja kaubandust tsiviilvastutuse harmoneeritud s&uuml;steemi alusel toimuva kaubanduse h&otilde;lbustamise vahel; seega on k&otilde;nealune aidanud t&otilde;sta kaubandusringkondade teadlikkust tooteohutuse ja sellele omistatava t&auml;htsuse k&uuml;simuses; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas the degree of harmonisation of Member States' laws achieved by Directive 85/374/EEC is not complete in view of the derogations provided for, in particular with regard to its scope, from which unprocessed agricultural products are excluded; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) direktiiviga 85/374/EM&Uuml; saavutatud liimesriikide &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamiseaste ei ole t&auml;ielik, pidades silmas s&auml;testatud erandeid, eriti pidades silmas direktiivi reguleerimisala, mis ei h&otilde;lma t&ouml;&ouml;tlemata p&otilde;llumajandustooteid; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas the Commission monitors the implementation and effects of Directive 85/374/EEC and in particular its aspects relating to consumer protection and the functioning of the internal market, which have already been the subject of a first report; whereas, in this context, the Commission is required by Article 21 of that Directive to submit a second report on its application; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) komisjon j&auml;lgib direktiivi 85/374/EM&Uuml; rakendamist ja m&otilde;ju ning eriti selle tarbijakaitse ning siseturu toimimisega seostu aspekte, mida on juba k&auml;sitletud esimeses aruandes; sellega seoses n&otilde;uab nimetatud direktiivi artikkel 21, et komisjon esitaks selle kohaldamise kohta teise aruande; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas including primary agricultural products within the scope of Directive 85/374/EEC would help restore consumer confidence in the safety of agricultural products; whereas such a measure would meet the requirements of a high level of consumer protection; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) p&otilde;llumajandussaaduste h&otilde;lmamine direktiivi 85/374/EM&Uuml; reguleerimisalasse aitaks taastada tarbijate usaldust p&otilde;llumajandustoodete ohutuse vastu; selline meede vastaks k&otilde;rgetasemelise tarbijakaitse n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas circumstances call for Directive 85/374/EEC to be amended in order to facilitate, for the benefit of consumers, legitimate compensation for damage to health caused by defective agricultural products; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) olukord n&otilde;uab direktiivi 85/374/EM&Uuml; muutmist, et h&otilde;lbustada tarbijatele puudulike p&otilde;llumajandustoodetega p&otilde;hjustatud kahju &otilde;igusp&auml;rast h&uuml;vitamist; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas this Directive has an impact on the functioning of the internal market in so far as trade in agricultural products will no longer be affected by differences between rules on producer liability; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) k&auml;esolev direktiiv m&otilde;jutab siseturu toimimist, kuiv&otilde;rd p&otilde;llumajandustoodetega kauplemist ei m&otilde;juta enam erinevused tootja vastutuse eeskirjades; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas the principle of liability without fault laid down in Directive 85/374/EEC must be extended to all types of product, including agricultural products as defined by the second sentence of Article 32 of the Treaty and those listed in Annex II to the said Treaty; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) direktiivis 85/374/EM&Uuml; s&auml;testatud tahtlusest s&otilde;ltumatu vastutuse p&otilde;him&otilde;tet tuleks laiendada k&otilde;igile tooteliikidele, kaasa arvatud asutamislepingu artiklis 32 m&auml;&auml;ratletud ja nimetatud lepingu II lisas loetletud p&otilde;llumajandustooted; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas, in accordance with the principle of proportionality, it is necessary and appropriate in order to achieve the fundamental objectives of increased protection for all consumers and the proper functioning of the internal market to include agricultural products within the scope of Directive 85/374/EEC; whereas this Directive is limited to what is necessary to achieve the objectives pursued in accordance with the third paragraph of Article 5 of the Treaty, </inglise>
<eesti> 9) vastavalt proportsionaalsuse p&otilde;him&otilde;ttele on k&otilde;igi tarbijate t&otilde;husama kaitse ja siseturu n&otilde;uetekohase toimimise p&otilde;hieesm&auml;rkide saavutamiseks vajalik ja sobiv arvata p&otilde;llumajandustooted direktiivi 85/374/EM&Uuml; reguleerimisalasse; k&auml;esolevas direktiivis piirdutakse sellega, mis on vajalik asutamislepingu artikli 5 kolmandas l&otilde;igus s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rkide saavutamiseks, </eesti>
<inglise> HAVE ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
